casebody.data:
Manuel DAVIS, Employee, Plaintiff-Appellant
v.
GREAT COASTAL EXPRESS, Employer, Defendant-Appellee.
Liberty Mutual Insurance Company, Carrier, Defendant-Appellee. No. 238P05. Supreme Court of North Carolina. June 30, 2005. Thomas F. Ramer, for Manuel Davis. James R. Martin, Gastonia, for Express & Insurance.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed on the 9th day of May 2005 by Plaintiff in this matter for discretionary review of the decision of the North Carolina Court of Appeals pursuant to G.S. 7A-31, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the North Carolina Court of Appeals:

"Denied by order of the Court in conference, this the 30th day of June 2005."
